SIMPLE: survive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Survive
<hw>Sur*vive"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Survived</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Surviving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>survivre</ets>, L. <ets>supervivere</ets>; <ets>super</ets> over +
<ets>vivere</ets> to live. See <er>Super-</er>, and
<er>Victuals</er>.]</ety> <def>To live beyond the life or existence of;
to live longer than; to outlive; to outlast; <as>as, to <ex>survive</ex>
a person or an event</as>.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p> <q>I'll assure her of⟦br⟧
Her widowhood, be it that she <qex>survive</qex> me,⟦br⟧
In all my lands and leases whatsoever.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Survive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Survive
<hw>Sur*vive"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To remain alive; to continue
to live.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy pleasure,⟦br⟧
Which, when no other enemy <qex>survives</qex>,⟦br⟧
Still conquers all the conquerors.</q> <rj><qau>Sir J.
Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Alike are life and death,⟦br⟧
When life in death <qex>survives</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Survivency</ent>⟦br⟧
